measures.name: residential_simulation_controls
measures.description: Set the simulation timesteps per hour and the run period begin/end month/day.
measures.modeler_description: Set the simulation timesteps per hour on the Timestep object, and the run period begin/end month/day on the RunPeriod object.

arguments.name: begin_day_of_month
arguments.display_name: Run Period Begin Day of Month

arguments.name: end_day_of_month
arguments.display_name: Run Period End Day of Month

measures.name: build_existing_model
measures.description: Builds the OpenStudio Model for an existing building.
measures.modeler_description: Builds the OpenStudio Model using the sampling csv file, which contains the specified parameters for each existing building. Based on the supplied building number, those parameters are used to run the OpenStudio measures with appropriate arguments and build up the OpenStudio model.

arguments.name: building_id
arguments.description: The building number (between 1 and the number of samples).

arguments.name: workflow_json
arguments.description: The name of the JSON file (in the resources dir) that dictates the order in which measures are to be run. If not provided, the order specified in resources/options_lookup.tsv will be used.

arguments.name: number_of_buildings_represented
arguments.description: The total number of buildings represented by the existing building models.

arguments.name: sample_weight
arguments.description: Number of buildings this simulation represents.

arguments.name: downselect_logic
arguments.description: Logic that specifies the subset of the building stock to be considered in the analysis. Specify one or more parameter|option as found in resources\options_lookup.tsv. When multiple are included, they must be separated by '||' for OR and '&&' for AND, and using parentheses as appropriate. Prefix an option with '!' for not.

measures.name: apply_upgrade
measures.description: Measure that applies an upgrade (one or more child measures) to a building model based on the specified logic.
measures.modeler_description: Determines if the upgrade should apply to a given building model. If so, calls one or more child measures with the appropriate arguments.

arguments.name: upgrade_name
arguments.description: User-specificed name that describes the upgrade.

arguments.description: Specify the parameter|option as found in resources\options_lookup.tsv.

measures.name: utility_bill_calculations
measures.description: Calculate utility bills for simple and detailed electricity tariffs.
measures.modeler_description: Calculate electric utility bills based on either: (a) monthly fixed charge and marginal rate, or (b) tariff from the OpenEI Utility Rate Database (URDB). Calculate other utility bills based on fixed charges for gas, and marginal rates for gas, oil, and propane. User can specify PV compensation types of 'Net Metering' or 'Feed-In Tariff', along with corresponding rates.

arguments.name: electric_bill_type
arguments.description: Choose either 'Simple' or 'Detailed'. If 'Simple' is selected, electric utility bills are calculated based on user-defined fixed charge and marginal rate. If 'Detailed' is selected, electric utility bills are calculated based on either: a tariff from the OpenEI Utility Rate Database (URDB), or a real-time pricing rate.

arguments.name: custom_tariff
arguments.display_name: Electricity: Custom Tariff or Real-Time Pricing Rate File Location
arguments.description: Absolute path to custom tariff or real-time pricing rate file. See resources/tariffs.zip for example tariff files. See resources/Sample Real-Time Pricing Rate.json for example real-time pricing rate file. Only applies if Tariff is 'Custom Tariff' or 'Custom Real-Time Pricing Rate'.

arguments.name: elec_fixed
arguments.description: Monthly fixed charge for electricity.

arguments.name: elec_rate
arguments.description: Price per kilowatt-hour for electricity. Use 'auto for state-average value from EIA.

arguments.name: gas_fixed
arguments.description: Monthly fixed charge for natural gas.

arguments.name: gas_rate
arguments.description: Price per therm for natural gas. Use 'auto for state-average value from EIA.

arguments.name: oil_rate
arguments.description: Price per gallon for fuel oil. Use 'auto for state-average value from EIA.

arguments.name: prop_rate
arguments.description: Price per gallon for propane. Use 'auto for state-average value from EIA.

arguments.name: pv_compensation_type
arguments.description: The type of compensation for PV.
choice_values: Net Metering
Feed-In Tariff
choice_display_names: Net Metering
Feed-In Tariff

choiceDisplayNames: Net Metering
Feed-In Tariff

arguments.name: pv_annual_excess_sellback_rate_type
arguments.display_name: PV: Net Metering Annual Excess Sellback Rate Type
arguments.description: The type of annual excess sellback rate for PV. Only applies if the PV compensation type is 'Net Metering'.
choice_values: retail electricity cost
user-specified
choice_display_names: retail electricity cost
user-specified

choiceDisplayNames: retail electricity cost
user-specified

arguments.name: pv_sellback_rate
arguments.display_name: PV: Net Metering Annual Excess Sellback Rate
arguments.description: The annual excess sellback rate for PV. Only applies if the PV compensation type is 'Net Metering' and the PV annual excess sellback rate type is 'user-specified'.

arguments.name: pv_tariff_rate
arguments.description: The annual full/gross tariff rate for PV. Only applies if the PV compensation type is 'Feed-In Tariff'.

measures.name: server_directory_cleanup
measures.description: Removes a significant portion of the saved results from each run, helping to alleviate memory problems.
measures.modeler_description: Use during large server runs, when individual sequel files and the like will not be needed.
